# Intuition
Inspired by https://leetcode.com/problems/strange-printer/solutions/233067/python-recursive-approach-with-memorization/, with a bit clean up.

> For each character at the end of the string, lets consider 2 cases:

> It was simply inserted with the cost of 1
It was free from some previous step to the left that printed this character already (we can print extra character all the way till the end)

# Code
```
class Solution:
    def strangePrinter(self, s: str) -> int:

        @cache
        def recur(s):
            if not s:
                return 0

            cost = recur(s[:-1]) + 1
            last_ch = s[-1]
            for i,c in enumerate(s[:-1]):
                if c == last_ch:
                    cost = min(cost, recur(s[0:i+1])+ recur(s[i+1:-1]))
            return cost

        return recur(s)

```

