approach : using recursive with divided and conquer + memoization

https://leetcode.com/problems/strange-printer/solutions/233067/python-recursive-approach-with-memorization/ 


- take CABBA 
- if you start from end, then there two possibilities for A 
    - A has cost of 1 and then print CABB 
    - A has cost of 0 due to previous A, so then it is based on cost of CA + BB 

```
    result[i] = min (

            1 + getMinCost(0 -> i-1), // 1 + CABB

            getMinCost(left -> i) + getMinCost(i + 1 -> right)) 
                                    if s.charAt(j) == s.charAt(i) // CA + BB

        )
```

# Complexity
