**Method 1:** Brute force DFS. Gets TLE
* Have two pointers left (L) and right (R) which track the turns print string s[L, R]
* Starting from `L + 1`, find the first char which is not s[L]. Let its index be i 
* Let f(x, y) denote minimum turns required to print s[x, y]
* There are two possible ways of achieving the final result
	* Case 1: Print s[L, i] in 1 turn, then print s[i + 1, R] recursively, so turns T = 1 + f(i + 1, R)
	* Case 2: 
		* This is greedy case, where we have another pointer `j` moving from i to R to find the next occurence of s[L], say at index j
		* When such an index is found, then s can be printed in 2 parts: s[i, j- 1] and s[j, R]
		* so T = f(i, j - 1) + f(j, R)
		* Notice that the turns to print s[L, i - 1] will be covered in s[j, R] because s[L, i - 1] comprise of the same character repeatedly which is the same as s[j]
* Minimum turns = min(turns for case 1, turns for case 2)
* This can better explained with an example, will do it later when I have spare time.
* IMO, this is a tough problem and is labelled hard for good reason. Pat yourself in the back if you understood any solution, let alone solving it by yourself
```
public int strangePrinter(String s) {
	return minTurns(s, 0, s.length() - 1);
}

private int minTurns(String s, int left, int right) {
	if (left == right)
		return 1;

	var i = left + 1;
	for (; i <= right && s.charAt(i) == s.charAt(left); i++);

	if (i == right + 1)
		return 1;

	var turns = 1 + minTurns(s, i, right);

	for (var j = i; j <= right; j++)
		if (s.charAt(j) == s.charAt(left)) 
			turns = Math.min(turns, minTurns(s, i, j - 1) + minTurns(s, j, right));

	return turns;
}
```
**Method 2:** Inject memoization in method 1
>**T/S:** O(n\xB3)/O(n\xB2), where n = size(s)
```
public int strangePrinter(String s) {
	return minTurns(s, 0, s.length() - 1, new HashMap<>());
}

private int minTurns(String s, int left, int right, Map<Pair, Integer> memo) {
	if (left == right)
		return 1;

	var key = new Pair(left, right);
	if (memo.containsKey(key))
		return memo.get(key);

	var i = left + 1;
	for (; i <= right && s.charAt(i) == s.charAt(left); i++);

	if (i == right + 1)
		return 1;

	var turns = 1 + minTurns(s, i, right, memo);

	for (var j = i; j <= right; j++)
		if (s.charAt(j) == s.charAt(left)) 
			turns = Math.min(turns, minTurns(s, i, j - 1, memo) + minTurns(s, j, right, memo));

	memo.put(key, turns);
	return turns;
}
```
